<br>
I have no sense of what anything is worth in this game. I've seen a lot of people say that money comes easily in AO but I don't see that happening for me.<br>
<br>
Is Q30ish meta and kevlar worth 5k a piece? What about Q30ish MA armor?<br>
<br>
I see the auctions for Bau and the amount people are paying and I can't believe it. 15k for a Q24 piece? Is it that valuable?<br>
<br>
I alway try to take the mindset that something is worth whatever someone is willing to pay for it but I really feel like I'm getting shafted.<br>
<br>
On another note, what is up with the auction style sales now? Can't someone just say &quot;This is what I want for this piece.&quot; and sell it? Instead everyone does this &quot;QX XXXXXXXXXX Bid is now at 12k.&quot; crap.  I'm not sure why this bugs me so much but it does. I've even seen it with low quality Cyber armor.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/ukezzic.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kezzic</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Tiny Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 37<br> <font color=#660000>(7/26/01 2:17:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=37.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Buying and Selling. Am I getting screwed?</span><hr size=1> The easy out answer is that an item is worth whatever someone will pay for it.<br>
<br>
From my own experience buying, selling and watching the auctions, the only items that regularly command &quot;premiums&quot; (which I define as prices above 100cr per QL) are Bau armor, Waitt armor, Freedom Arms 3927 pistols, sunglasses and armor above QL45 or so.  The others, from the stuff that no one wants (Nail armor) to the stuff that is wanted (MA armor) see a lot more fluctuation.  I have seen QL30 MA armor sell for 3000, and then for 5000.<br>
<br>
I think in part this is because there are still not too many of a given item; once there is a more steady supply I think prices will fluctuate less (and be lower).<br>
<br>
Occasionally I will get an item that I know will fetch big prices.  For these I tend to do an auction (&quot;bid currently at ...&quot;), just because I will get more that way than if I try to guess how high someone will go.  While the prices we see for things like Bau do seem out of whack when compared to other armor types sold by players, merchants charge so much more that the PC traded items don't seem like such a bad deal.  And I believe there are some folks for whom buying from merchants remains an alternative, so plopping down 10k for a QL20 item might actually save a bit of money.<br>
