on't need it and they do so theres no reason to make &quot;all&quot; my money off one person.<br>
B: I firmly believe that if you hook people up then later on when you need help..you get remembered. C: Most the people usually end up asking if I have anything else to sell and then will buy more than one item of me. (cause they know they'll get it at a cheaper price) D: Most of the people I sell to also send me an occasional tell asking me if I have anything to sell...and every business man knows repeat customers are great for keeping business pumping.<br>
So if you hang out in Tir then you've prob seen me around.<br>
If you are looking to sell stuff just make sure your not trying to make a ton of cash off the sale of a couple items. <br>
As far as buying goes...if you know what you are looking for I'd suggest at bare minum do some research on the item..just ask people that have the item you want how much they paid for it...is it worth what they paid for it...(performance wise).<br>
Also alot of item prices depends on where you are located. I've been to newland....prices there are inflated alot compared to the prices in Tir. ( MY main office of sales :P )<br>
Well hope this helps some...if not...sorry <br>
